For me, being a woman means RESILIENCE. [the capacity to withstand or to recover quickly from difficulties; toughness.] 

From the first time I set foot on a Track and competed in hurdles l knowing I would have to work harder than everyone else being legally blind in my left eye to going through so many trials and tribulations in the journey of becoming a mother. Our resilience and capability to wipe our tears off and get up and work harder every single day is the what makes us women unstoppable and incomparable.

hunger and food insecurity every day. 
Women are hungrier despite often being the ones who work the hardest. Today, I for International Women’s Day, I wanted to share the six ways women are hungrier. 

For food. For equality. For change.

I’m not a fan of Yoga and Pilates but I couldn’t deny how amazing my body felt after taking them. Which is why I became certified and then created my own fusion of the two + barre 5 years ago. My clients love it and the playlist that comes with the sweat sesh (r&b, slow beats and Afro beats). 

It’s back Mondays at 6pm!

What is Flowlicious: 
Flolwlicious is a restorative, low impact flow class that incorporates barre, pilates, core work, and yoga movements to best r&b and slow beats. The workout program is tailored to create a stronger core and tone. You don’t need any gadgets, but if you have a mat, #DreaApproved resistance bands, gliders and 3lb dumbbells it would be a great addition to take the class to the next level.
